dcterms:description: The Urban Dynamometer Driving Schedule (UDDS) is utilized in the learning as the vehicle operating conditions, providing a standard driving cycle for evaluating vehicle performance.
dcterms:title: Urban Dynamometer Driving Schedule (UDDS)

dcterms:description: The Worldwide Harmonized Light Vehicles Test Cycle (WLTC) is used as a validation driving cycle to compare the fuel economy results of the Q-learning supervisory control against the ECMS supervisory control.
dcterms:title: Worldwide Harmonized Light Vehicles Test Cycle (WLTC)

dcterms:description: The Highway Fuel Economy Test (HWFET) is also used as a validation driving cycle to compare the fuel economy results of the Q-learning supervisory control against the ECMS supervisory control.
dcterms:title: HWFET (Highway Fuel Economy Test)
